translateTo

public PolyglotPersistentBean translateTo(java.util.Locale locale)
Creates a copy of current object with different language. The copy is connected to the current object via the Translation object they share. You will want to overwrite this method if you want to duplicate collections etc. If you do so, make sure to call the method of this base class (super.createTranslatedObject(locale)) to ensure that the language and the translation stuff is set correctly. Additionally this copies the values of all basic fields (Integer, Long, Float, Double, Boolean, String and Date) to the new object. If you use a SecurityManager, only public fields can be copied, otherwise all fields will be copied (even private ...)

Parameters:
locale - The language to translate to. If locale.language equals the language of the current object, the object itself (this) is returned and no copy is created.
Returns:
a flat not persisted copy of the object, or the object itself, or null if locale is null
